'''Krist<U+00ED>na Ku<U+010D>ov<U+00E1>''' (born [[May 23]], [[1990]] in [[Bratislava]]) is a junior [[tennis player]] from [[Slovakia]]. Her highest juniors ranking has been '''World Number 3'''. According to the [[International Tennis Federation]], Kucov<U+00E1>'s favorite type of court is the [[clay court]], she hits a two-handed forehand and backhand (like Wimbledon finalists [[Marion Bartoli]] and [[Monica Seles]]), and her father, Jozef Ku<U+010D>a, also coaches her.

==Tennis career==
===Juniors===
At the [[2007 U.S. Open (tennis)|2007 U.S. Open]], the unseeded Kucov<U+00E1> stunned everyone by taking the title, defeating thirteenth seed [[Julia Glushko]] in the third round, top seed and defending champion [[Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova]] in the quarterfinals, and number two seed [[Urszula Radwa<U+0144>ska]] in the final, 6<U+2013>3, 1<U+2013>6, 7<U+2013>6 (4). In addition to this, Ku<U+010D>ov<U+00E1> reached the [[2007 Wimbledon Championships]] and [[2007 French Open]] girls' doubles quarterfinals. Both times, Kucov<U+00E1> was seeded seventh, however, she reached the French Open quarterfinals with compatriot [[Klaudia Boczova]], losing to eventual champions and third seeds [[Ksenia Milevskaya]] and Urszula Radwa<U+0144>ska. She reached the [[The Championships, Wimbledon|Wimbledon]] quarterfinals along with compatriot [[Lenka Jurikova]]. The seventh-seeded Slovakian pair lost to eventual runner-ups [[Misaki Doi]] and [[Kurumi Nara]], 7<U+2013>5, 6<U+2013>3.

